From 587b1fd6664bbfa8d056e619622e25a8155b7e0b Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Slick <slick@slicksync.local>
Date: Mon, 13 Jul 2026 05:52:26 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] feat+fix: Nebula default theme (redone) + accurate watch
 duration

The previous v1.9.37 tag pointed at the wrong commit (identical to
v1.9.36) - the Nebula default-theme change never actually landed
despite the tag existing and deploying successfully. Redone properly
here: ThemeContext default, useState initial, localStorage fallback,
and CSS :root selector all changed from slick to nebula.

Combined with the accurate-duration work: live 'Watching for Xm' and
permanently-stored durationSeconds both compute from real
watched-content position delta instead of wall-clock/checkpoint
timestamp math. Added lastPosition/totalDuration to WatchSession as a
direct position/runtime snapshot (inspired by reviewing
Sonicx161/AIOManager's approach) - more robust against sparse
provider checkpoints than a derived elapsed-time value.

Bump to 1.9.37 (replacing the mispointed tag), changelog updated.
